<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">
The keyword field can be used in one of 2 ways:<br>
<br>
<b>1) Simple Search:</b> simply type in your keywords, separated by spaces and select "Any Words", "All Words" or "Exact Phrase" from the pull-down menu next to it. DO NOT type in any special characters or words such as AND, OR, NOT, ", ', (, ) etc...<br>
<br>

<b>2) Advanced Boolean Search:</b> If you select this option from the pull-down menu, you can then type in a boolean search string. This will require that you have basic knowledge about boolean search syntax. There are a few rules:<br>
<br>
<li>Each keyword / phrase must be enclosed by DOUBLE QUOTES -> "xxxx"</li>
<li>To build complex expressions, you must enclose logical groupings in parentheses -> ("xxxxx" OR "yyyyy")</li>
<li>You must make use of the keywords <b>AND</b>, <b>OR</b> and <b>AND NOT</b> to build your search string</li><br>
<br>

<b>For example:</b><br>
<br>
-Type in: "network engineer" AND ("Novell" OR "Windows")<br>
<br>
This will return resumes that contain the exact phrase "network engineer", as well as: 1) either the keyword "Novell" or 2) the keyword "Windows".
